    "evolutionary_en": "The soul arrived through Neptune's dissolving waters carrying concentrated intention around the great Piscean question: what remains of the individual when the boundary between self and other grows genuinely thin? The stellium here suggests an election to undergo the full force of that dissolution and discover not annihilation but a more permeable form of selfhood — compassion not as sentiment but as a mode of knowing that cannot be separated from the known.",
    "developmental_en": "The shadow in Pisces concentration is the dissolution that never re-forms — the compassion that becomes self-erasure, the sensitivity that becomes a reason to withdraw, the visionary capacity turned inward until it loses contact with the world it was meant to illuminate. The developmental task is to find the spine within the wave: to bring Piscean depth into grounded, crafted, specific form that can actually reach others.",
    "aphorism_en": "The ocean does not cease being the ocean when it agrees to become a river."
