    "planet": "",
    "sign": "virgo",
    "house": "",
    "traditional_en": "A planetary concentration in Virgo traces through biography as an abiding care for how things are done — the methods, the details, the gap between what is and what might be refined into something more precise. Service and craft appear as central themes, and the inner life is often marked by a discriminating intelligence that notices fault lines and possibilities that others pass by without seeing.",
    "evolutionary_en": "The soul chose the Mercurial-Chironic field of Virgo as its primary laboratory because this life carries the task of refinement at a fundamental level — not correction as criticism but discrimination as a healing act. The concentration suggests an intention to develop the capacity to hold the ideal and the actual in the same gaze without flinching from either, bringing the world into closer alignment with what it could become through patient, exacting attention.",
    "developmental_en": "The shadow of Virgo concentration is the critic turned entirely inward or outward without relief — an inability to rest in what is sufficient, a perfectionism that prevents completion. The developmental direction is toward the recognition that refinement serves something larger than itself, and that the instrument must sometimes set down its tools and trust that the work done is enough for this day's offering.",
    "aphorism_en": "The finest grain of salt knows it does not salt the sea, only the meal placed before a living person."
