    "sign": "astral-body",
    "house": "",
    "traditional_en": "Before the capacity for self-reflection arrives, there is desire. The pull toward warmth, the recoil from threat, the surge of excitement that precedes any reasoning about it — this is the domain of the astral body, the soul-carrier that the human being shares in its general structure with the animal kingdom, though in the human being it carries additional dimensions the animal does not. Classical astrology reads this layer through the interplay of Mars and Venus, and through the fire and air signs: Aries and Scorpio for the drive-life, Libra and Gemini for the relational and communicative feeling-tones, Leo for the vital warmth of self-expression. The aspects these planets form to each other and to the angles of the chart describe the internal weather of the feeling life — its characteristic storms and its characteristic silences.\n\nFrom a developmental perspective, the astral body is neither liability nor gift in itself — it is the medium through which all soul experience initially arrives. Passion, grief, desire, inspiration, dread: they all pass through this layer first, before the reflecting I has had any opportunity to meet them. The task across a lifetime is not suppression but progressive education — the slow development of a feeling life that can be held consciously rather than simply undergone.\n\nThe natal Mars-Venus configuration indicates the particular flavour of this layer's challenge: where drive and desire are in natural alignment, where they create productive friction, and where unexamined emotional habits tend to run ahead of conscious intention. The configuration describes the terrain; what is made of it remains genuinely open.",
