    "traditional_en": "There is a capacity in the human being that no other creature possesses in the same way: the ability to stand back from one's own reactions, to observe the part of oneself that is reacting, and to introduce a response that was not simply given by the situation or by habit. The ancient traditions called this spark of individuality the highest of the human members — uniquely human, uniquely responsible, uniquely free. The astrological tradition encodes it in the Sun — not as personality or as character, but as the conducting principle that can, over time, bring the other bodies into coherent relationship with one another rather than allowing each to run on its own terms.\n\nThe Sun's sign, house, and aspects describe the mode and arena in which this capacity for self-directed development tends to become conscious and effective. A Sun developing through a fire sign in the angle of visible life will meet its task quite differently than a Sun working through an earth sign in the house of hidden processes — not better or worse in any absolute sense, but with a different set of resistances and a different style of eventual mastery.\n\nCritically, the 'I' is not something the person already fully is at birth — it is something the person is in the process of becoming across the whole span of a life. The solar placement indicates the particular mode this soul elected for that becoming: the challenges it chose to meet, the arena where the work of self-direction will show its results most visibly, and the quality of authority that becomes available when the work has been genuinely done.",
    "evolutionary_en": "",
    "developmental_en": "",
