    "house": "",
    "traditional_en": "The relationship between Ascendant and Sun describes the meeting between how a soul arrives in the world and what it came to embody. The Ascendant is the vehicle; the Sun is the cargo. When these are in compatible elements, the outer manner serves the inner fire without great resistance, and purpose flows through personality naturally. When they are in tension, the soul learns — often slowly — that what the world sees is not the obstacle to who one is, but the very medium through which purpose becomes tangible and real.",
    "evolutionary_en": "The evolutionary work is to stop experiencing the Ascendant as a constraint on the Sun — or the Sun as something hidden behind the Ascendant. In more developed souls these two become seamlessly integrated: the way one moves through the world becomes exactly how the soul mission expresses itself. The mask and the mission stop being separate things. They become one continuous gesture, indistinguishable from each other.",
    "developmental_en": "Practically: notice where you feel you must hide your true purpose behind a social presentation, or conversely, where you lead with solar intensity in ways that bypass the more refined vehicle the Ascendant offers. The work is integration — letting the form serve the fire, and the fire illuminate the form.",
